The paper deals with privacy-preserving inference of DNN models in the cloud service, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The solution proposed in the paper combines homomorphic encryption and Bayesian neural networks, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions experiments conducted on a clinical dataset, which suggests a potential application in cybernetics (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE).
